Here's the full **testsmells.org 19-smell** audit of `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs`, calibrated for integration tests (`[TestCategory("Integration")]`).

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smells Found | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| High | 3 | 3 |
| Medium | 1 | 1 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **4** | **4** |

**4 of 8 tests are smell-free** — `UpdateUser_ModifiesExistingRecord`, `DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase`, `ListUsers_ReturnsAllInserted`, and `InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity` are well-structured with clear AAA separation, proper assertions, and good naming.

---

## High-Severity Findings

### 1. Assertion-Free Test (a.k.a. Unknown Test) — `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors`

**Lines 112–119** · The test inserts 100 users but never asserts anything. It passes as long as no exception is thrown, giving false confidence that bulk insertion actually works.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — no assertion, test always passes
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
}

// ✅ Fix — verify the inserts actually persisted
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, users.Count);
}
```

**Risk:** The repository's `Insert` could silently swallow errors or no-op; this test would still report green.

---

### 2. Sleepy Test — `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay`

**Line 87** · `Thread.Sleep(3000)` introduces a fixed 3-second wait. If the notification mechanism is faster, you waste time; if it's slower on CI, you get flaky failures.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — fixed sleep, non-deterministic
Thread.Sleep(3000);
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));

// ✅ Fix — poll with timeout using a retry loop
var deadline = DateTime.UtcNow.AddSeconds(5);
while (DateTime.UtcNow < deadline)
{
    if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
        break;
    await Task.Delay(100);
}
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id),
    "Notification was not sent within the 5-second timeout.");
```

**Integration-test calibration:** Async coordination is expected in integration tests, but `Thread.Sleep` with a hardcoded duration is still a smell — polling/retry is the standard pattern. Severity remains **High**.

---

### 3. Conditional Test Logic — `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType`

**Lines 101–108** · The `if/else` means only one branch ever executes per run. Since a basic `User` is inserted (not a `PremiumUser`), the `if` branch with `DiscountRate` is **dead code** — never tested.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — one branch is always dead
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}

// ✅ Fix — split into two focused tests
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_BasicUser_ReturnsCorrectName()
{
    var user = new User("eve@example.com", "Eve");
    _repository.Insert(user);
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasPositiveDiscount()
{
    var user = new PremiumUser("vip@example.com", "VIP", discountRate: 0.1m);
    _repository.Insert(user);
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("vip@example.com") as PremiumUser;

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk:** The `PremiumUser` discount logic is completely unverified despite appearing in the test.

---

## Medium-Severity Findings

### 4. Assertion Roulette — `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase`

**Lines 35–38** · Four assertions with no message parameters. When one fails in CI, the stack trace gives only a line number — not which property was wrong.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — which assertion failed?
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);

// ✅ Fix — add descriptive messages
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert.");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip.");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip.");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Auto-generated Id should be positive.");
```

---

## Smells Scanned — No Issues Found (15 of 19)

| # | Smell (testsmells.org name) | Result |
|---|---|---|
| 2 | **Mystery Guest** | ✅ Clean — in-memory SQLite, no external files/services |
| 5 | **Eager Test** | ✅ Clean — each test calls ≤ 3 production methods |
| 6 | **Magic Number Test** | ✅ Clean — `3` and `10` in count assertions are self-evident from preceding inserts |
| 7 | **Sensitive Equality** | ✅ Clean — no `ToString()` comparisons |
| 8 | **Exception Handling** | ✅ Clean — no `try`/`catch` in tests |
| 9 | **General Fixture** | ✅ Clean — `_connection` and `_repository` are used by every test |
| 10 | **Ignored Test** | ✅ Clean — no skipped tests |
| 11 | **Duplicate Assert** | ✅ Clean — no repeated identical assertions |
| 12 | **Lazy Test** | ✅ Clean — each test targets a distinct behavior |
| 13 | **Constructor Initialization** | ✅ Clean — uses `[TestInitialize]` correctly |
| 14 | **Default Test** | ✅ Clean — class is properly named |
| 15 | **Redundant Print** | ✅ Clean — no `Console.WriteLine` |
| 16 | **Redundant Assertion** | ✅ Clean — no tautological assertions |
| 17 | **Resource Optimism** | ✅ Clean — no assumptions about external resources |
| 18 | **Empty Test** | ✅ Clean — no empty method bodies |

---

## Positive Observations

- **Excellent test isolation** — in-memory SQLite with per-test `[TestInitialize]`/`[TestCleanup]` means zero cross-test contamination
- **`sealed` test class** — prevents unintended inheritance hierarchies
- **Good naming convention** — `Method_Scenario_Expected` used consistently (e.g., `DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase`)
- **Proper cleanup** — `_connection.Dispose()` in `[TestCleanup]` prevents resource leaks
- **Concurrency test** — `InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity` tests a real integration concern

---

## Prioritized Remediation

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Effort |
|----------|-------|-----|--------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add count assertion to `BulkInsert` | 2 min |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into two focused tests | 5 min |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with poll loop | 5 min |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | Add message strings to 4 assertions | 2 min |

**Bottom line:** Half your tests are clean and well-designed. The four smells above are straightforward fixes — priorities 1–3 eliminate false-confidence and flakiness risk, while #4 is a diagnostic-clarity improvement.
